    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text means — moving from observation (what does it say?) to discerning the Chronicler's intent in his original post-exilic context. The movements below trace the chapter's argument from its tribal prologue through the climactic Saul genealogy. This is not a narrative chapter but a genealogical argument, and arguments must be read as wholes, not merely as lists of data-points.",
